National Universities Commission (NUC) has approved Shehu Shagari University of Education, Sokoto as the 58th state university and 206th university in Nigeria. Presenting the certificate of recognition yesterday in Abuja to Sokoto State Governor Aminu Tambuwal, the executive secretary of the NUC, Prof. Adamu Rasheed, said it is the first university of education in northern Nigeria and 4th of its kind in the country. Responding, Tambuwal said the university will be entrepreneurship based and will focus on functional and effective education. He said, “The university will help in empowerment and human capital development of the people of Sokoto State.” The governor added that the university already passed recommendations of upgrade before the state House of Assembly, adding that his administration had complied with the necessary documentations.